frameDefinitions: A Process comes to an end.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to continue.
A Process of using or modifying is scheduled to be applied to a group or mass.
An Item comes to be attached to a Goal, with a Connector forming a bond between the Handle of the Item and the Goal (or some part of it).
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to end.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
frameExamples: The goaltenders <t>kept</t> the game going with terrific saves.
Three more cars <t>remain</t> to be fixed.
According to plan, the front part of the hull quietly <t>attached</t> to the docking gear.
Bush may <t>lift</t> sanctions on his own, despite opposition.
listRoleDefinitions: Name of the event which occurs.
When the event ends.
Where the event takes place.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> to continue or the <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
A <fen>Process</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
The time at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The location at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The activity that is being applied to the mass or the set of entities.
The mass or group that has not yet been processed.
The time when the <fen>Remainder</fen> is assessed.
<fen>Connector</fen> identifies the  instrument used to attach, usually in a <ment>with</ment>-PP.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that comes to be attached to the <fen>Goal</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are tied together, resulting in their mutual attachment.
<fen>Goal</fen> identifies the location to which the first <fen>Item</fen> is attached.
The time when the attaching event takes place.
The location where the attaching event takes place.
A <fen>Process</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
A <fen>State</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is ended.
The location where the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is caused to end.
A concrete or abstract <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> of an <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>State</fen> is found to still persist.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the <fen>State</fen>.
listRoleExamples: The soot in the air  kept <fex>it</fex> <fex>raining</fex> for weeks
<fex>The storm</fex> kept us in all the next day.
An additional eighty-three invitations remain <fex>to be sent</fex>
In this case everyone should be informed by word of mouth to contact the person holding the list to find out <fex>which gifts</fex> still remain to be bought.
<fex>Now</fex> only three more items remain to be sold
The remoras attach to the whale <fex>with their strong jaws</fex>.
The remoras attach <fex>to the underside of the whale</fex>.
<fex>That move</fex> ended her political career, she said in a 1994 Times Union interview.
They ended their relationship <fex>in the same coffeehouse where it started</fex>.
Martial law remains in effect <fex>in Absurdistan</fex>.
